Former eThekwini mayor Zandile Gumede and co-accused R300 million tender case continues. eNCA's Dasen Thathiah. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede's corruption and fraud trial resumes on Tuesday at the KwaZulu-Natal High Court. It kicked off on Monday following a number of delays. READ: More charges against Zandile Gumede The first witness is expected to take the stand on Tuesday. Gumede and her 21 co-accused face a string of charges including fraud and corruption relating to the awarding of a Durban Solid Waste tender worth over R300 million.